  static const String buyingNewVehicle =
      '''<p>Buying a new car gets you the benefit of the latest advances in safety and security, comfort, performance and fuel efficiency and you'll be able to get just the specification you want.</p>
  <p>Once you've decided which car you want to buy, do some research online so that when you go into the dealership or speak to the vendor you are in a strong position to haggle. Look to see if there are any similar cars for sale elsewhere and compare the prices. Even if you are buying a brand new car, the dealer will have room for manoeuvre on the price.</p>
  <p>Remember there is always room for negotiation when it comes to car prices, especially in the current climate, so decide how much you are prepared to pay for the vehicle (but be realistic) and stick to your guns. Be prepared to walk away though if this price isn't agreed - with a bit of luck you'll get a phone call from the seller or dealer agreeing to your terms.</p>
  <p>Dealers will work a lot harder if they think they're going to get a deal so let them know you're there to buy a car if the deal is right. However, don't come across as desperate to buy as this could reduce your chances of picking up a bargain - play it cool.</p>
  <p>Don't forget running costs when buying a car. Diesel cars offer better fuel economy but they cost more to buyer, as does the fuel, so you may need to cover thousands of miles before you save money.</p>
  <p>Make sure any special features or extras you want are included in the price</p>
  <p>Remember your budget - don't get carried away</p>
  <p><strong>Buying a car with cash</strong></p>
  <p>This is the simplest car-buying option if you have the funds to spare. But don't assume that cash is king - car dealers make more money from finance customers.</p>
  <p>If you're buying a new car with cash, don't brag about it. Instead, let the dealer think you are considering finance, until you've agreed the bottom-line price for the car.</p>
  <p>Don't hand over money until you're satisfied with the collection or delivery arrangements.</p>
  <p>Don't be pressured into buying - walk away if you're not completely happy.</p>
''';

  static const String buyingUsedVehicle = '''
<p>We've put together some simple tips in helping you secure your dream car.</p>
<p><strong>Do your research</strong> - Always find out as much information about the car. How much you will have to pay for insurance, fuel, road tax and many others. Are there any common faults with this vehicle that you should check? Of course, in the age and time of the internet, these facts are easier to find than they used to be.</p>
<p><strong>Check the seller</strong> - Once you've found a potential car, there are a few simple things you can do to help check that you are dealing with a legitimate seller. Remember, whilst cars purchased from a dealer will be a little more expensive, you do benefit from certain amount of extra legal protection should there be a problem with your purchase.</p>
<p>When calling a <strong>private seller, </strong>ask about 'the car'. If they ask you 'which car' then you may be dealing with a dealer that is trying to pretend otherwise, thus avoiding their legal obligations. Make sure you are able to visit the car at the seller's home or business premises if they are a dealer.</p>
<p>Ask thorough questions about the car, its past and current conditions.</p>
<p>Always arrange to view a private sale at the seller's house (daytime) or public area and if it's a dealer at their premises.</p>
<p>Don't view a car in the rain, poor light or at night. You won't be able to check the condition of the car properly if it's wet - water hides scratches, dents and other problems therefore make sure you see the car clearly and from all angles. <strong>NEVER VIEW A CAR AT NIGHT FOR SAFETY REASONS</strong></p>
<p>Ask about the service history of the car.</p>
<p>Thoroughly assess the documentation of the car to ensure the authenticity of it.</p>
<p>Be careful of car cloning - In some cases a car can be given the identity of another by replacing the number plate with those from similar identical car - same make, model, year and colour. <strong>Be Warned!</strong></p>
<p>Be wary of anything that seems like a real bargain, or has a very low mileage for its age. There will always be bargains but in general, if a deal looks too good to be true then it most likely is.</p>
<p>Don't be pressured into buying a car. There are always other vehicles out there so if don't satisfied in any way it's time to walk away.</p>
<p>Be wary of and don't be influenced by statements like change of job, moving abroad, relationship break-up, new baby on the way - hence bigger car, etc. etc. The point is you're buying the car to help yourself and not anyone else.</p>
<p>Before you hand over any money, do the following;</p>
<ul>
<li>Agree collection/delivery arrangements</li>
<li>Confirm exactly what's included in the price</li>
<li>Confirm any work that the seller has agreed to do</li>
<li>Make sure you get the full documents of the car and a receipt detailing the price, date and time of sale, terms of sales and the seller's details.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Be a good buyer</strong> - Turn up on time for your viewing, make prompt but wise decision (having done all the appropriate checks and always go with someone)</p>
''';

  static const String safetyNotice =
      '''<p>Buying or selling a car or car part/accessories should be an enjoyable and stress free experience, and with AutoTitanic we go the extra mile to ensure that your journey in securing a good and reliable car or car part is made smooth and safe. Our safety advice and tips will ensure you stay secure online, whether you are a buyer or seller of a car or car parts &amp; accessories.</p>
  <p>Keep things local by meeting face to face</p>
  <p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>How do I stay safe when using Autotitanic.com?</strong></p>
  <p>We have noticed that one of the best ways to stay safe is to ensure that all transactions take place locally, in-person and with cash. Remember that Autotitanic.com is your local classifieds website and advertisements are not always reviewed before they go live on our site. Therefore, we would advise that you take the following precautionary measures when visiting the Autotitanic.com</p>
  <ul>
<li>When buying or selling, you should always meet in-person to see the vehicle or the part/accessory. Meeting in a public place with many people around is quite essential. If possible, meet at a bank for a safe transaction.</li>
<li>Never send or wire money to sellers or buyers. This includes mailing a cheque or using payment services such as Credit/Debit card, Western Union, Money Gram, PayPal, Google Wallet/Checkout, etc. While this site is very useful and secure, scammers will pretend to use them and even go to the extent of falsifying documents from a legitimate company.</li>
<li>Never give out your personal or banking information over the internet.</li>
<li>Use common sense. If something sounds too good to be true, it probably is.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Tips for Sellers</strong></p>
<ul>
